        <p><strong>The Cave:</strong> The natural limestone cave contains the three self-manifested (<em>Swayambhu</em>) rock formations. The central form is flanked by the other two — an aniconic representation of the triple-goddess that may predate formal Hinduism and connect to prehistoric cave worship traditions of the northwestern Himalayan foothills.</p>
