        <p><strong>Historical Patronage:</strong> Shivaji made significant donations and built additions to the temple complex. Subsequent Peshwa rulers continued patronage. The temple was a target during the Mughal invasions of the Deccan — its protection was a matter of Maratha political honor and religious identity simultaneously.</p>
