      <div class="card-details">
        <p><strong>Legend:</strong> Ravana performed a 1000-year penance to Shiva at this spot, offering his ten heads one by one into the sacrificial fire. When the tenth was to be offered, Shiva appeared and healed all his heads, granting Ravana the boon of being the greatest devotee of Shiva. Shiva then manifested here as Vaidyanath — "Lord of Healing" — though the circumstances of how the linga remained here involve Vishnu's clever intervention against Ravana taking it to Lanka.</p>
        <p><strong>Shravan Mela:</strong> The most extraordinary pilgrimage event in Jharkhand — during the holy month of Shravan (July-August), approximately 3–4 crore (30–40 million) pilgrims walk barefoot up to 100 km from the Ganga at Sultanganj to Deoghar, carrying sacred Ganga water in decorated pots (<em>kanwar</em>) to offer at Vaidyanath. This is one of the world's largest annual religious events.</p>
