  <div class="highlight-section" style="margin-top:3rem;">
    <div class="concept-title" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">🌟 Kings Who Protected Dharma — Hall of Honor</div>
    <div class="concept-grid" style="margin-top:1rem;">
      <div style="padding:1rem; border-left:2px solid var(--gold);">
        <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif; color:var(--gold); margin-bottom:.5rem;">Vikramaditya (Chandragupta II)</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">Patronized Kashi and the great sacred sites of North India during the Gupta golden age. The Gupta period is when the canonical forms of Shiva and Shakti iconography were established.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:1rem; border-left:2px solid var(--gold);">
        <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif; color:var(--gold); margin-bottom:.5rem;">Krishnadevaraya (Vijayanagara)</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">The greatest patron of South Indian temples in the medieval period. His donations to Srisailam, Tirupati, and Rameshwaram are recorded in copper plate inscriptions. He personally undertook pilgrimage to every major South Indian sacred site.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:1rem; border-left:2px solid var(--gold);">
        <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif; color:var(--gold); margin-bottom:.5rem;">Ahilyabai Holkar (Maratha)</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">The single greatest temple patron in Indian history — rebuilt Kashi Vishwanath, Grishneshwar, Somnath, and hundreds more. Her personal devotion and political vision made temple restoration a matter of civilizational survival.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="padding:1rem; border-left:2px solid var(--gold);">
        <div style="font-family:'Cinzel',serif; color:var(--gold); margin-bottom:.5rem;">Nara Narayana (Koch Dynasty)</div>
        <p style="font-size:.85rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">Rebuilt Kamakhya in 1565 CE after Kala Pahar's destruction — the most important single act of temple reconstruction in Northeast Indian history. His patronage saved the supreme Tantric site of the Indian world.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
